pr_title: Options button features in API updated
pr_body:
@pradeeban

- It can be noticed that "chmod +x \*/\*" is added to makestudy and makedocker scripts. It is because when I executed them in the newly installed Ubuntu 20.04, a permission denied error was coming even while executing all methods (even from CLI).

- Moreover, (after makestudy is executed) for any posix system, the interpreter directive (shebang) is not present in the scripts of params and unlock. The same goes for the case of makedocker execution, for any script created the interpreter directive (shebang) is absent. Therefore, I made some changes in [mkconcore.py](https://github.com/Rahuljagwani/concore/blob/main/mkconcore.py). If you remember in Friday's meeting I was getting an error **Exec format error: './build'**, it was because of this issue only. Even though from CLI we are able to execute them, but not from API calls.

Let me know if there are any other ways to deal with it or any changes.
Thank You
